@database RANDOM
@FONT COURIER.FONT 13
@INDEX "index.guide/main"
@NODE Main "RANDOM"
@TOC "rexx.guide/Built-In FUNCTION LIBRARY INDEX"
@{b}RANDOM()@{ub}

Usage:@{b}RANDOM([min],[max],[seed])@{ub}

Returns a pseudo-random integer in the interval specified by the min and max
arguments. The default minimum value is 0 and the default maximum value is 999.
The interval max-min must be less than or equal to 1000. If a greater range of
random integers is required, the values from the @{"RANDU()" LINK "RANDU/main"} function can be suitable
scaled and translated.

The seed argument can be supplied to initialize the internal state of the
random number generator.

See also: @{"RANDU()" LINK "RANDU/main"}

Example:
@{fg shine}
        thisroll = random(1, 6)  /* might be 1   */

        nextroll = random(1, 6)  /* snake eyes?  */
@{fg text}
@ENDNODE
